description: Based deep in Burbank, California, 10 Forward Productions is an animation studio skillfully practicing all aspects of production. Whether it's pre-production, post-production or concept development, the 10 Forward team is always ready and equipped to face the challenge with confidence and professionalism. Among the services we offer are: writing, storyboarding, animatics, character design, editing, sound design, music scoring, animation, comics and motion graphics. Aside from the studio's work on mobile game projects, music videos and TV productions, 10 Forward also works on its own IP developments including graphic novels, web comics, and animated pilots for TV and web.
name: 10 Forward Productions, Inc.

description:
Space Coast Comixx is a publishing outfit based in Central Florida. They mainly publish the free comic series titled Space Coast Comixx that can be picked up in several locations throughout Brevard, Osceola, Orange and many other counties. The series itself has a main storyline called Demon in a Spacesuit, but it also acts as an anthology series, which allows other creators to contribute stories to the series, along with reprinting classic stories too.

Notable people have worked with Space Coast Comixx, Nino Mesarina, Pete Hernandez III, Martin Dunn, Charlie Apenllaniz, and many others.

Space Coast Comixx was the brainchild of Jake Estrada. After years of working in the underground indie scene of comics, he decided to create a series that could be read by many people, and have the product placed into many hands.

His approach is unique in itself as many comics aren't distributed in this approach. Originally when the first series hit, it was only distributed in Melbourne Florida. It wasn't long before it expanded and took over the entire county of Brevard. Then breaching into other counties, and expanding into Chicago, NJ, Philadelphia and many more areas.

The comic series is always in color, and printed on high gloss paper stock.

Space Coast Comixx has a large stable of characters and books on the horizon and is a champion of creator rights and creations. In the very near future is will be releasing the best of Nino Mesarina collection, who is the creator of The Unbelievable Laundrey Detergent Man.
name: Space Coast Comixx
